race.comment: Competitive. MEGA FIGHT (7) didn't feature in town but turned the form around winning a 58 at Nowra over a mile and looked good doing it. Should relish the step up in trip and tumbles in weight. That brings him right into it. GWENDIE (10) deserves another win and there was only a half-length in it at Newcastle over 1850 the latest. Maps well and gets her chance. MY GREEK GOD (3) won that race, spiking his figures.  Peaks now and should also run the middle distance right out. Just needs average luck from the awkward barrier. JUST GO BANG (1) won a 64 at Hawkesbury two back over this distance from the speed. That effort stacks up and he has a handy 3kg claim. On a 9-day backup and has to be considered. DEVILS DAUGHTER (9) didn't do a bad job last start over 2140m at Goulburn beaten 2.25L. That followed a win at Bathurst. Draws well and has claims.
